## Acceptance Criteria

1. `createDb()` accepts optional pool configuration parameters.
2. Default pool settings: max=10, idle timeout=30s, connection timeout=10s.
3. SSL is enforced for RDS connections.
4. `getDb()` returns the same Drizzle instance on repeated calls (singleton verified).
5. Drizzle ORM queries work end-to-end: dashboard -> pool -> RDS.
6. Connection works from local dev machine.
7. Connection works from the VPS.
8. Pool releases idle connections after timeout.
9. Pool handles exhaustion with a clear timeout error (not an infinite hang).
